history.content: You shouldn't need to re-add to the waitlist.  If you are waitlisted for a discussion and lab that have space, you should be enrolled automatically. If you are not enrolled by Wednesday or Thursday, reach out to Lydia Raya in 205 Cory who is managing EE enrollments.

I've been on the waitlist for ee16a since phase 1, and my major declaration went through a few days ago. We have been told that all declared CS and EECS students should get into the class, and I am now part of this group. Do I need to re-add myself to the waitlist now tat I am a declared CS major, or will my status automatically be updated? thanks
